I am using flame1.m in Matlab to calculate the stand off distance for a 
burner flame.  I need to know the thermal conductivity at each grid 
point.  The command, thermalConductivity(gas) returns the thermal 
conductivity of the gas at the final grid point.  The command, solution
(fl, 'flow', thermalConductivity(gas)) returns a list containing the 
correct number of entries, but they are not even close to the correct 
values (the first point is 500, and most of the rest are 0).  My 
ultimate goal is to write a csv file containing the velocity, 
temperature, and thermal conductivity profiles.  This is easy on 
Python, but I still have not figured out how to import solutions into 
python to use as an initial guess.  Does anyone know how to get the 
thermal conductivity at each grid point in Matlab, or how to import 
solutions as initial guesses in Python?  

Thank you very much for any help you can offer.

Jeff Miller

Colorado School of Mines Engineering
